          favorite song, eh?  Well that's pretty obvious for me, i think.  Paranoid Android is THE Stairway to Heaven of the 90's.  You can practically break that song down in to 3 different parts:  (1)Folky/Melodic guitar work that makes up the first part and sets forth the story of the song.  (2) The harsh middle/outro dominated by angry power chords and, dare I say, SQUISHY guitar solo, and (3) the break down that follows afterwards that sounds almost like a sort of eulogy ("rain down, from a great height").  And awesome lyrics.  I'm just waiting for my opportunity to call someone a "kicking, screaming, gucci little piggi".<br /><br />Other favorites include Life in a Glass House (gotta love the whole new orleans funeral feel of that one), Street Spirit, and How to Disappear Completely (listening to it is like listening a living instrument stuggling to hit a certain note; cool stuff).  <br /><br />I'd love to get my hands on more of their B-sides, but they're hard to come across, and i don't like buying singles, feeling they're not worth the money.  They need to just release an entire B-sides album, a la Build Something Out of Nothing.  <br /><br />Other great bands that i think are similar to Radiohead are Sigur Ros, Clinic, Beta Band and, in a way, Blur(those guys are very underrated).<br /><br />On another note i bought the new Cure album today; very cool stuff.  It's got a sort of early 90's grunge feel to it, combined with the classic gothy Cure sound.  And now that Lollapalooza's been canned (sadly), Curiosa Festival stands as the best festival this summer.  Oy, can't wait to see Interpol.<br /><br />Wow, look at how fast i broke from the topic w/ that last paragraph.  Meh.  <br />
